This is a remake by me of the original cs_deagle5 from 1.6.  The structure of the map has been kept in tact.  Players start with full body armor and a deagle with full ammo.  The map does support 16 players on each side, but that could get chaotic.

cs_deagle5 is not a complicated map, but usually simple maps lead to more fun.

So i screwed up whole skybox so it turned black :( I try to change it and release v2

So theres lots of spot lights and dust floating in air. Also lots of dark spots. Working elevator from 1st floor to roof

Players spawn within a cellular structure with breakable walls which give access to other cells within the map.

Both teams are split into two groups and spawn at opposite ends of the map.

There is no way of predicting which end your team mates have spawned at, so be careful and make sure that you don't end up having to reload as soon as a wall has broken open.

Thanks To The Maker Of cs_castleball_usa For Making The Map.
Thanks To Some Friends For Helping Me With Ideas.

It's time to play the Gungame version of that classic "Chutes And Ladders" game.
We have Chutes, Ladders, a Spinner, some Dice, and 4 Player Pieces on the board.
Except in this version, the players are looking to headshot each other!!!

Note: You can only go DOWN the Chutes but the Ladders are bi-directional.
And the GravPipe in the center only softens the landing.
Also, there are Hidden Teleports - so watch that platform leaping.

~~~ Worm

6. Double Click on 'maps'
